==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Refrigeratory
<hw>Re*frig"er*a*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-ries</plw> <pr>(-fr<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[CF. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧frig⟦eacute⟧ratoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>That which
refrigerates or cools.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>In
distillation, a vessel filled with cold water, surrounding the worm, the
vapor in which is thereby condensed.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
chamber, or tank, in which ice is formed, in an ice machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refrigerium</ent>⟦br⟧
